We introduce a fast high-order method for evaluating hyperbolic potentials arising in time-domain wave propagation. The algorithm decomposes the computation into local and history components using a smoothly windowed representation and accelerates the history term using a truncated Fourier series with fast transforms, achieving near-linear scaling in time for large-scale wave scattering problems.
